Is there a function that verifies if an extent has been removed?
`extentp' cannot be used for that: 

-------------------- *scratch* --------------------

(setq ext (make-extent 1 (point)))
#<extent [1, 35) (flags=0x0) in buffer *scratch*>

(extentp ext)
t

(delete-extent ext)
nil
ext
#<destroyed extent>
(extentp ext)
t
